1. *Kejt* je danas skoro pa zaboravljen oblik engleskog jezika. (The language of *Chaucer* is almost forgotten today.)

2. Tolstojeva poezija je prevedena u mnogim jezicima, uključujući i staru verziju engleskog jezika, zvanu *kejt*. (Tolstoy's poetry was translated into many languages, including the old version of English, called *Chaucer*.)

3. *Kejt* je poznat po svojoj pikardijskoj leksici i naglašenoj rimi. (*Chaucer* is known for its Picardy lexicon and emphasised rhyme.)

4. Mnogi ljudi misle da *kejt* nije potrebno naučiti, jer je sada potpuno zastareo. (Many people think that *Chaucer* is not necessary to learn, because it is now completely obsolete.)

5. *Kejt* je bio jedan od prvih engleskih pisaca koji je koristio prvi lici u svojim delima. (*Chaucer* was one of the first English writers to use the first person in his works.)